    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood from the species Quercus michauxii, a valuable North American bottomland timber tree of the Atlantic and Gulf coastal plains and Mississippi Valley region; so-named because the wood is often cut into strips and used for making baskets.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
